<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 08 at 10:54PM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF SOUTHEASTERN
SHERIDAN, NORTHWESTERN KIDDER AND NORTHERN BURLEIGH COUNTIES THROUGH
1130 PM CDT...
At 1054 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Wing, or 22
miles south of Mcclusky, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Wing around 1100 PM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
